We are try gin to compile last year code that contains yagsl.
when compiling the code we have that error:

FAILURE: Build failed with an exception.

* Where:
Build file '/Users/sylvain/Robotics_Repo/team8626_2024/build.gradle' line: 88

* What went wrong:
Could not determine the dependencies of task ':jar'.
> Could not resolve all files for configuration ':runtimeClasspath'.
   > Could not find swervelib:YAGSL-java:2024.6.1.0.
     Searched in the following locations:
       - file:/Users/sylvain/wpilib/2024/maven/swervelib/YAGSL-java/2024.6.1.0/YAGSL-java-2024.6.1.0.pom
       - https://frcmaven.wpi.edu/artifactory/vendor-mvn-release/swervelib/YAGSL-java/2024.6.1.0/YAGSL-java-2024.6.1.0.pom
       - https://broncbotz3481.github.io/YAGSL-Lib/yagsl/repos/swervelib/YAGSL-java/2024.6.1.0/YAGSL-java-2024.6.1.0.pom
       - https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/swervelib/YAGSL-java/2024.6.1.0/YAGSL-java-2024.6.1.0.pom
     Required by:
         project :

we suspect it is due to the vendor lid URL being: https://broncbotz3481.github.io/YAGSL-Lib/yagsl/yagsl.json and this file now point to lates library (2025)

Assuming our diagnosis is correct, what would be the correct URL to point to the 2024 .json file?

Or is there another way to fix this without importing the code top 2025 WPILib?
